Using Proper Datatypes
 - Examining the data types
 - ri.dtypes

stop_date             object
stop_time             object
driver_gender         object
driver_race           object
violation_raw         object
violation             object
search_conducted        bool	-True or False
search_type           object
stop_outcome          object
is_arrested           object
stop_duration         object
drugs_related_stop      bool	-True or False
district              object

Why do data type matter?
 - Affects which operation you can perform?
 - Avoid storing data as strings (when possible)
 	- int, float enables mathematical operations
 	- datatime, enables date-based method attributes
 	- category, uses less memory and runs faster
 	- bool: enables logical and mathematical operations

Fixing a datatype.
df.price.dtype.
dtype('O')

to change the data type of the variable.
df['price'] = df.price.astype('float')
apple.price.dtype
dtype('float64')

Bracket notation: apple['price']
Must be used on the left side of an assignment statement
